Definition: engaged in or accustomed to close observation
Example: caught by a couple of alert cops; alert enough to spot the opportunity when it came; constantly alert and vigilant, like a sentinel on duty
Synonyms: noun, state, alert, attribute, alertness, UNALERT, watchful, cognition, watchfulness, AWAKE, LIVELY, WARY, engaged, in, or, accustomed, to, close, observation, caught, by, a, couple, of, cops, enough, spot, the, opportunity, when, it, came, constantly, and, vigilant, like, sentinel, on, duty
Category: adj.all
